title.narrative: MULTI-SECTORAL NUTRITION

description.narrative: By 2022, multi-sectoral political commitments and approaches are in place to support prioritized, integrated, nutrition sensitive interventions with an equity focus in 4 most deprived S/R, conflict & disaster affected and peri-urban areas in Yangon, which contributes to Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more children under 5 and women of reproductive age equitably access and utilize evidence-based health, HIV & nutrition interventions, including adoption of key behaviours, especially among vulnerable populations in most deprived states/regions, conflict-affected and peri-urban areas (Goal Area 1 UNICEF Strategic Framework 2018-2021)

description.narrative: The Multi Sectoral National Plan of Action for Nutrition (MS-NPAN) costing and budget briefs for prioritized states and regions were drafted with substantial technical and financial support from UNICEF and National Nutrition Centre (NNC). UNICEF has been chairing SUN network, ensuring that the agreed framework of action for maternal nutrition and complementary feeding for Myanmar is implemented with the MS-NPAN. A stronger coordination mechanism and linkages with maternal and child cash transfer (MCCT), Early Childhood Development (ECD) , WASH, food systems and education was realized for maintaining essential nutrition services as response to COVID-19 pandemic. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/07/2020
